```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        error("Input must be of type DateTime. Given: $dt")
    end

    return dt + hours(bump)
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` input and an optional `bump` parameter (defaulting to 3 hours). It checks if the input is of the correct DateTime type, throwing an error for other types.

The function then adds the bump in hours to the original timestamp and returns the updated DateTime.
